# ovh_vps_disk

Manages monitoring settings on an existing OVHcloud VPS disk.

~> **NOTE** This resource does **not** provision an additional disk. Disks are
ordered through the `plan_option` block on the parent `ovh_vps` resource using
a `option-additional-disk-2025-XXXXg` plan code. `ovh_vps_disk` only manages the
two writable fields exposed by the API on an already-existing disk:
`monitoring` and `lowFreeSpaceThreshold`.

~> **NOTE** Because the API does not expose a way to delete a disk via this
endpoint, the `destroy` operation does not remove the underlying disk. Instead,
it resets `monitoring` to `true`, clears `low_free_space_threshold`, and removes
the resource from Terraform state. To actually remove the disk, remove the
corresponding `plan_option` block from the parent `ovh_vps` resource.

