## Argument Reference

* `service_name` - (Required, ForceNew) The internal name of the VPS (e.g.
  `vps-XXXXXX.vps.ovh.net`).
* `disk_id` - (Required, ForceNew) Numeric identifier of the disk attached to
  the VPS. The list of disk IDs can be retrieved via the `ovh_vps_disks` data
  source.
* `monitoring` - (Optional) Enable or disable OVHcloud monitoring on the disk.
* `low_free_space_threshold` - (Optional) Threshold (in MiB) below which a
  low-free-space alert is raised.

## Attributes Reference

The following attributes are exported in addition to the arguments above:

* `id` - `service_name|disk_id` composite identifier.
* `type` - Disk type (`primary` or `additional`).
* `state` - Disk state (`connected`, `disconnected`, `pending`).
* `size` - Disk size in GiB.
* `bandwidth_limit` - Disk bandwidth limit.

## Import

A VPS disk can be imported using the composite identifier `service_name|disk_id`:

```sh
terraform import ovh_vps_disk.disk vps-XXXXXX.vps.ovh.net|1234
```
